  "BodyEn": "\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Chr\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022captioned-image-container\u0022\u003E\u003Cfigure\u003E\u003Ca class=\u0022image-link image2 is-viewable-img\u0022 target=\u0022_blank\u0022 href=\u0022https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568605117036-5fe5e7bab0b7?crop=entropy\u0026amp;cs=tinysrgb\u0026amp;fit=max\u0026amp;fm=jpg\u0026amp;ixid=M3wzMDAzMzh8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwyfHxjYXJ8ZW58MHx8fHwxNzUwNzU0MzY4fDA\u0026amp;ixlib=rb-4.1.0\u0026amp;q=80\u0026amp;w=1080\u0022 data-component-name=\u0022Image2ToDOM\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022image2-inset\u0022\u003E\u003Cpicture\u003E\u003Csource type=\u0022image/webp\u0022 srcset=\u0022https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568605117036-5fe5e7bab0b7?crop=entropy\u0026amp;cs=tinysrgb\u0026amp;fit=max\u0026amp;fm=jpg\u0026amp;ixid=M3wzMDAzMzh8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwyfHxjYXJ8ZW58MHx8fHwxNzUwNzU0MzY4fDA\u0026amp;ixlib=rb-4.1.0\u0026amp;q=80\u0026amp;w=1080 424w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568605117036-5fe5e7bab0b7?crop=entropy\u0026amp;cs=tinysrgb\u0026amp;fit=max\u0026amp;fm=jpg\u0026amp;ixid=M3wzMDAzMzh8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwyfHxjYXJ8ZW58MHx8fHwxNzUwNzU0MzY4fDA\u0026amp;ixlib=rb-4.1.0\u0026amp;q=80\u0026amp;w=1080 848w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568605117036-5fe5e7bab0b7?crop=entropy\u0026amp;cs=tinysrgb\u0026amp;fit=max\u0026amp;fm=jpg\u0026amp;ixid=M3wzMDAzMzh8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwyfHxjYXJ8ZW58MHx8fHwxNzUwNzU0MzY4fDA\u0026amp;ixlib=rb-4.1.0\u0026amp;q=80\u0026amp;w=1080 1272w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568605117036-5fe5e7bab0b7?crop=entropy\u0026amp;cs=tinysrgb\u0026amp;fit=max\u0026amp;fm=jpg\u0026amp;ixid=M3wzMDAzMzh8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwyfHxjYXJ8ZW58MHx8fHwxNzUwNzU0MzY4fDA\u0026amp;ixlib=rb-4.1.0\u0026amp;q=80\u0026amp;w=1080 1456w\u0022 sizes=\u0022100vw\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568605117036-5fe5e7bab0b7?crop=entropy\u0026amp;cs=tinysrgb\u0026amp;fit=max\u0026amp;fm=jpg\u0026amp;ixid=M3wzMDAzMzh8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwyfHxjYXJ8ZW58MHx8fHwxNzUwNzU0MzY4fDA\u0026amp;ixlib=rb-4.1.0\u0026amp;q=80\u0026amp;w=1080\u0022 width=\u00225472\u0022 height=\u00223648\u0022 data-attrs=\u0022{\u0026quot;src\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568605117036-5fe5e7bab0b7?crop=entropy\u0026amp;cs=tinysrgb\u0026amp;fit=max\u0026amp;fm=jpg\u0026amp;ixid=M3wzMDAzMzh8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwyfHxjYXJ8ZW58MHx8fHwxNzUwNzU0MzY4fDA\u0026amp;ixlib=rb-4.1.0\u0026amp;q=80\u0026amp;w=1080\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;srcNoWatermark\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;fullscreen\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;imageSize\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;height\u0026quot;:3648,\u0026quot;width\u0026quot;:5472,\u0026quot;resizeWidth\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;bytes\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;alt\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;silver sports coupe on asphalt road\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;title\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;type\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;image/jpg\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;href\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;belowTheFold\u0026quot;:false,\u0026quot;topImage\u0026quot;:true,\u0026quot;internalRedirect\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;isProcessing\u0026quot;:false,\u0026quot;align\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;offset\u0026quot;:false}\u0022 class=\u0022sizing-normal\u0022 alt=\u0022silver sports coupe on asphalt road\u0022 title=\u0022silver sports coupe on asphalt road\u0022 srcset=\u0022https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568605117036-5fe5e7bab0b7?crop=entropy\u0026amp;cs=tinysrgb\u0026amp;fit=max\u0026amp;fm=jpg\u0026amp;ixid=M3wzMDAzMzh8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwyfHxjYXJ8ZW58MHx8fHwxNzUwNzU0MzY4fDA\u0026amp;ixlib=rb-4.1.0\u0026amp;q=80\u0026amp;w=1080 424w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568605117036-5fe5e7bab0b7?crop=entropy\u0026amp;cs=tinysrgb\u0026amp;fit=max\u0026amp;fm=jpg\u0026amp;ixid=M3wzMDAzMzh8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwyfHxjYXJ8ZW58MHx8fHwxNzUwNzU0MzY4fDA\u0026amp;ixlib=rb-4.1.0\u0026amp;q=80\u0026amp;w=1080 848w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568605117036-5fe5e7bab0b7?crop=entropy\u0026amp;cs=tinysrgb\u0026amp;fit=max\u0026amp;fm=jpg\u0026amp;ixid=M3wzMDAzMzh8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwyfHxjYXJ8ZW58MHx8fHwxNzUwNzU0MzY4fDA\u0026amp;ixlib=rb-4.1.0\u0026amp;q=80\u0026amp;w=1080 1272w, https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1568605117036-5fe5e7bab0b7?crop=entropy\u0026amp;cs=tinysrgb\u0026amp;fit=max\u0026amp;fm=jpg\u0026amp;ixid=M3wzMDAzMzh8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwyfHxjYXJ8ZW58MHx8fHwxNzUwNzU0MzY4fDA\u0026amp;ixlib=rb-4.1.0\u0026amp;q=80\u0026amp;w=1080 1456w\u0022 sizes=\u0022100vw\u0022 fetchpriority=\u0022high\u0022\u003E\u003C/picture\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cfigcaption class=\u0022image-caption\u0022\u003EPhoto by \u003Ca href=\u0022true\u0022\u003EErik Mclean\u003C/a\u003E on \u003Ca href=\u0022https://unsplash.com\u0022\u003EUnsplash\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/figcaption\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAbout a year and a half ago, I was searching for a used car to buy. Like many buyers, I was juggling factors like price, reliability, mileage, but one thing kept nagging at me more than anything else: \u003Cstrong\u003Esafety\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI began to wonder:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cem\u003EIs a Toyota safer than a Ford? What about Honda or Mazda?\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cbr\u003EThat curiosity led me down a rabbit hole that every data analyst\u2014or aspiring one\u2014knows too well: \u003Cstrong\u003Erealizing that asking the right question is half the job\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Chr\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Ch3\u003E\uD83D\uDE97 Step 1: Collecting Accident Data\u003C/h3\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMy first instinct was simple: download accident logs. I gathered datasets covering long periods from different regions. The data included information like the car involved, the crash\u0027s severity, and sometimes outcomes like injuries or deaths.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAt first glance, it seemed logical to start by \u003Cstrong\u003Ecounting the number of accidents per car brand\u003C/strong\u003E. But then I paused.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWould that tell me which brand is safer?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Chr\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Ch3\u003E\u26A0\uFE0F Realization: Raw Counts Are Misleading\u003C/h3\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf more Toyotas appear in accident reports, does that mean they are less safe?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOf course not.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere are far too many \u003Cstrong\u003Econfounding factors\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESome brands are simply more common on the road.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDriver behavior and skill levels vary.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ERoad and weather conditions are inconsistent.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENot all accidents are equal in severity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn short, \u003Cstrong\u003Eraw accident counts mean very little in isolation\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Chr\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Ch3\u003E\uD83E\uDDEE What About Fatalities?\u003C/h3\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESo I shifted my focus:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cem\u003EMaybe I should look at the number of deaths per brand?\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAgain, not quite. Fatality counts alone are not helpful without context. I needed a \u003Cstrong\u003Eratio\u003C/strong\u003E: deaths relative to something meaningful\u200A\u2014\u200Aperhaps the \u003Cstrong\u003Enumber of serious accidents\u003C/strong\u003E that occurred within each brand.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBut that raised another question:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHow do I define a \u201Cserious\u201D accident?\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022captioned-image-container\u0022\u003E\u003Cfigure\u003E\u003Ca class=\u0022image-link image2 is-viewable-img\u0022 target=\u0022_blank\u0022 href=\u0022https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!evN3!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F88c5569e-db14-470c-b600-e7c907afca1a_1080x712.jpeg\u0022 data-component-name=\u0022Image2ToDOM\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022image2-inset\u0022\u003E\u003Cpicture\u003E\u003Csource type=\u0022image/webp\u0022 srcset=\u0022https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!evN3!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F88c5569e-db14-470c-b600-e7c907afca1a_1080x712.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!evN3!,w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F88c5569e-db14-470c-b600-e7c907afca1a_1080x712.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!evN3!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F88c5569e-db14-470c-b600-e7c907afca1a_1080x712.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!evN3!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F88c5569e-db14-470c-b600-e7c907afca1a_1080x712.jpeg 1456w\u0022 sizes=\u0022100vw\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!evN3!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F88c5569e-db14-470c-b600-e7c907afca1a_1080x712.jpeg\u0022 width=\u00221080\u0022 height=\u0022712\u0022 data-attrs=\u0022{\u0026quot;src\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/88c5569e-db14-470c-b600-e7c907afca1a_1080x712.jpeg\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;srcNoWatermark\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;fullscreen\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;imageSize\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;height\u0026quot;:712,\u0026quot;width\u0026quot;:1080,\u0026quot;resizeWidth\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;bytes\u0026quot;:156323,\u0026quot;alt\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;grayscale photo of horse on grass field\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;title\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;type\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;image/jpeg\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;href\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;belowTheFold\u0026quot;:true,\u0026quot;topImage\u0026quot;:false,\u0026quot;internalRedirect\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;isProcessing\u0026quot;:false,\u0026quot;align\u0026quot;:null,\u0026quot;offset\u0026quot;:false}\u0022 class=\u0022sizing-normal\u0022 alt=\u0022grayscale photo of horse on grass field\u0022 title=\u0022grayscale photo of horse on grass field\u0022 srcset=\u0022https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!evN3!,w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F88c5569e-db14-470c-b600-e7c907afca1a_1080x712.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!evN3!,w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F88c5569e-db14-470c-b600-e7c907afca1a_1080x712.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!evN3!,w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F88c5569e-db14-470c-b600-e7c907afca1a_1080x712.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!evN3!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F88c5569e-db14-470c-b600-e7c907afca1a_1080x712.jpeg 1456w\u0022 sizes=\u0022100vw\u0022 loading=\u0022lazy\u0022\u003E\u003C/picture\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cfigcaption class=\u0022image-caption\u0022\u003EPhoto by \u003Ca href=\u0022true\u0022\u003ERobin Battison\u003C/a\u003E on \u003Ca href=\u0022https://unsplash.com\u0022\u003EUnsplash\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/figcaption\u003E\u003C/figure\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Chr\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Ch3\u003E\uD83E\uDDF1 Defining the Right Metric\u003C/h3\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEventually, I landed on a question that made much more sense:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWhat is the ratio of death cases to strong (severe) crashes, broken down by car brand?\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis approach eliminated minor crashes from the equation and focused only on situations where the car\u2019s \u003Cstrong\u003Estructural integrity and safety features\u003C/strong\u003E truly mattered.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt wasn\u2019t perfect, but it was much closer to a \u003Cstrong\u003Efair and meaningful comparison\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Chr\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Ch3\u003E\uD83D\uDCCA The Result? No Clear Winner\u003C/h3\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAfter analyzing the data with this new question in mind, the outcome was humbling:\u003Cbr\u003EMost car brands performed similarly.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere was no clear winner in terms of overall safety at the brand level.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis led me to a final realization\u2026\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Chr\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Ch3\u003E\uD83D\uDD0D I Was Asking Too Broad a Question\u003C/h3\u003E\u003Cp\u003EComparing entire brands\u200A\u2014\u200Alike Toyota vs. Ford\u200A\u2014\u200Ais a bit like comparing \u201Cfruit\u201D to \u201Cvegetables.\u201D There\u2019s just too much variation within each category.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe smarter question would have been:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIs a Mazda 3 safer than a Honda Civic?\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDrilling down to the \u003Cstrong\u003Emodel level\u003C/strong\u003E\u200A\u2014\u200Anot the brand\u200A\u2014\u200Ais where the insights live.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Chr\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Ch3\u003E\uD83E\uDDE0 Key Lesson: Data Alone Isn\u2019t Enough\u003C/h3\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis experience taught me something crucial that I now apply to every data project:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EYou don\u2019t get valuable answers from data until you ask the right question.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\u2019s tempting to dive headfirst into charts and metrics. But the first\u200A\u2014\u200Aand most important\u200A\u2014\u200Astep in any analysis is \u003Cstrong\u003Edefining a question that makes sense within the context\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOtherwise, you might be chasing numbers that lead you nowhere.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Chr\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Ch3\u003E\u270D\uFE0F Final Thoughts\u003C/h3\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhether you\u2019re shopping for a car, evaluating performance at work, or analyzing customer behavior, data can only take you so far.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EClarity begins with curiosity. Insight begins with asking the right question.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022subscription-widget-wrap-editor\u0022 data-attrs=\u0022{\u0026quot;url\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;https://rami13kh.substack.com/subscribe?\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;text\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;Subscribe\u0026quot;,\u0026quot;language\u0026quot;:\u0026quot;en\u0026quot;}\u0022 data-component-name=\u0022SubscribeWidgetToDOM\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022subscription-widget show-subscribe\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022preamble\u0022\u003E\u003Cp class=\u0022cta-caption\u0022\u003EThanks for reading! Subscribe for free to receive new posts and support my work.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cform class=\u0022subscription-widget-subscribe\u0022\u003E\u003Cinput type=\u0022email\u0022 class=\u0022email-input\u0022 name=\u0022email\u0022 placeholder=\u0022Type your email\u2026\u0022 tabindex=\u0022-1\u0022\u003E\u003Cinput type=\u0022submit\u0022 class=\u0022button primary\u0022 value=\u0022Subscribe\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022fake-input-wrapper\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022fake-input\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022fake-button\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/form\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E",
